Happy Birthday Bill. My best friend and confidant. These were the words of Rachel Ruto, the wife of deputy president William Ruto. Via a post on Twitter, Rachel said she cannot repay the amount of love Ruto who turned 53, has given her. "This day is special as we celebrate your birthday and our wedding anniversary. This far we have come all I can say is thank you. Nothing I can do can repay the amount of love ..." she said. "My prayer for you as we go forward is Numbers 6:24-26 .The Lord bless you and keep you; the Lord make his face shine on you and be gracious to you; the Lord turn his face toward you and give you peace.” Elgeyo Marakwet senator Kipchumba Murkomen also wished Ruto well as he enjoys his day. "Happy birthday boss, dedicate to you that memory versus in Josh.1:9,the one you used to teach in Sunday School remember? “Have I not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage; do not be afraid, nor be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.” Digital New Media director at the Presidential Strategic and Communication Unit Dennis Itumbi also wished Ruto well. “Happy Birthday boss. You are a friend. A true friend… For 9 years you have always offered your guidance, mentorship and most importantly friendship," he said. He added "There are no ups and downs when it comes to you, you call, listen, admonish, share stories and each time any of us is down you call and literally cheer us up." 